Here's the revised code that includes a counter for the beans grabbed, a button for making bribes, and random starting beans. The amount of beans will increase after each successful bribe:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Thief Caravans Game</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            color: #333;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            margin: 10px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        #result {
            margin-top: 20px;
            font-size: 1.2em;
        }
        #beansCount {
            font-size: 1.5em;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Thief Caravans Game</h1>
<p>Can you find and steal from the caravans? Click the button to search for a caravan!</p>

<button id="searchButton">Search for a Caravan</button>
<button id="bribeButton">Make a Bribe</button>

<div id="result"></div>
<div id="beansCount">Beans Grabbed: 0</div>

<script>
    const searchButton = document.getElementById('searchButton');
    const bribeButton = document.getElementById('bribeButton');
    const resultDiv = document.getElementById('result');
    const beansCountDiv = document.getElementById('beansCount');

    let totalBeans = Math.floor(Math.random() * 500) + 50; // Random starting amount between 50 and 549
    let beansGrabbed = 0;

    const caravans = [
        { loot: 100, caught: false },
        { loot: 50, caught: false },
        { loot: 200, caught: false },
        { loot: 30, caught: false },
        { loot: 0, caught: true }, // Represents a caravan where the player got caught
    ];

    searchButton.addEventListener('click', function() {
        // Randomly choose a caravan
        const caravan = caravans[Math.floor(Math.random() * caravans.length)];

        // Determine the result
        if (caravan.caught) {
            resultDiv.innerHTML = "Oh no! You got caught while trying to steal!";
            // Disable the button since you can't search anymore
            searchButton.disabled = true;
            bribeButton.disabled = true; // Disable bribe button as well
        } else {
            beansGrabbed += caravan.loot;
            totalBeans -= caravan.loot;
            resultDiv.innerHTML = "Success! You stole " + caravan.loot + " beans!";
            beansCountDiv.innerHTML = "Beans Grabbed: " + beansGrabbed;
        }
    });

    bribeButton.addEventListener('click', function() {
        const bribeAmount = Math.floor(Math.random() * 50) + 10; // Random bribe between 10 and 59
        totalBeans += bribeAmount;
        resultDiv.innerHTML = "You made a bribe and received " + bribeAmount + " beans!";
        beansCountDiv.innerHTML = "Beans Grabbed: " + beansGrabbed;
    });
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Key Features:
1. **Beans Counter**: A counter shows the total beans grabbed after successful thefts.
2. **Bribe Button**: A button that allows players to make bribes, which increases their total beans by a random amount (10 to 59) each time it's clicked.
3. **Random Starting Beans**: The starting amount of beans is randomly generated between 50 and 549.

This setup should provide a fun and interactive experience for players!

Here's the updated code that allows players to make a bribe after being caught in order to continue stealing. I've also added a display for the last bribe amount:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Thief Caravans Game</title>
    <style>
        body {
